    <bug_when>2008-02-19 16:54:38 -0500</bug_when>
    <thetext>After further discussion with Lifeng, we decided to still launch the Filter dialog from the same Filter button on the chart data page that is used for regular data sets.  However, the chart cube Filter dialog will only show those dimensions or measures that are currently used in the chart.  Therefore, if the user has not dragged any items to the value, category, or series fields, the Filters button will be disabled.  
This way, users will always filter data from the same place, whether they are using a cube or not.  The Filter dialog for the chart cube will not use the terms &quot;dimension&quot; or &quot;measure&quot; but will instead show a drop list displaying &quot;Category&quot;, &quot;Series&quot;, or &quot;Value&quot;, depending on which of these the user has already defined in the chart.  Therefore, we don&apos;t need the radio set that is at the top of the Crosstab filter dialog.  </thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
